dynatax_skills_categorizer	dynatax_skills	DynaTax: Intelligent skill inference and job matching through inductive reasoning. Derives implicit competencies from career context (Session 1) then scores job match quality with gap analysis and recommendations (Session 2). Primary facet: ri (induce - 50%), secondary facets: gs (score - 30%), ce (extract - 10%), rc (cost-benefit - 5%), ot (template - 5%).	=== DYNATAX PROMPT SCRIPT (2-Session Architecture) ===\n\nSESSION 1: DERIVE_ALL_SKILLS (isolated, phi3:latest, ~12s)\n\nAnalyze this career profile and extract ALL skills - both explicitly stated AND implicitly demonstrated.\n\nCAREER PROFILE:\n{career_profile_text}\n\nFor each skill:\n1. Identify the skill name\n2. Provide evidence from the text showing this skill\n3. Rate confidence: high/medium/low\n4. Categorize: technical/business/creative/interpersonal\n\nInclude skills that are IMPLIED by the work described, even if not explicitly stated.\n\nEXAMPLE OF IMPLICIT INFERENCE:\n"Managed software licenses for 80,000 users"\n IMPLIES: SQL, Database Management, Vendor Management, Compliance, Scale Operations, Reporting\n\nReturn JSON array:\n[\n  {\n    "skill": "skill_name",\n    "evidence": "quote or description from profile showing this skill",\n    "confidence": "high/medium/low", \n    "category": "technical/business/creative/interpersonal"\n  }\n]\n\nCRITICAL: Return ONLY the JSON array, no commentary, no code fences.\n\n\n\nSESSION 2: MATCH_JOB_TO_PROFILE (isolated, phi3:latest, ~3s)\n\nIMPORTANT: Use isolated session with explicit output passing (NOT continuous context).\n\nYou previously extracted these skills from a candidate profile:\n\n{session_1_output}\n\nNow analyze how well they match this job:\n\nJOB REQUIREMENTS:\n{job_requirements_text}\n\nEvaluate the match between the candidate skills and job requirements.\n\nReturn JSON:\n{\n  "match_score": 0-100,\n  "matching_skills": ["skill1", "skill2", "skill3"],\n  "relevant_experience": "brief description of applicable experience",\n  "key_strengths": "what makes candidate strong for this role",\n  "gaps": "what is missing or needs development",\n  "recommendation": "STRONG/MODERATE/WEAK MATCH - specific actionable advice"\n}\n\nSCORING GUIDELINES:\n- 70-100: STRONG MATCH (most requirements met, minor gaps)\n- 40-69: MODERATE MATCH (core skills present, some gaps)\n- 0-39: WEAK MATCH (significant gaps, limited overlap)\n\nCRITICAL: Return ONLY the JSON object, no commentary, no code fences.\n\n\n\n=== TECHNICAL NOTES ===\n\nArchitecture: 2-session chain with isolated sessions + explicit passing\n- Session 1 PRIMARY facet: ri (induce) - inductive reasoning from examples\n- Session 2 PRIMARY facet: gs (score) - match quality evaluation\n\nProven Models:\n- phi3:latest: Session 1 (12s), Session 2 (3s) - use isolated sessions only\n- qwen2.5:7b: Untested candidate for Session 2 (stability comparison)\n\nKnown Issues:\n- phi3:latest with maintain_llm_context=1 (continuous) causes hallucinations after ~2 runs\n- Always use isolated sessions with explicit {session_1_output} substitution\n\nLibrary Catalog Classification:\n- PRIMARY: r  ri (reason/induce) - pattern recognition, implicit knowledge derivation\n- SECONDARY: gs (score), ce (extract), rc (cost-benefit), ot (template)\n- Shelve by PRIMARY capability, note SECONDARY uses in remarks\n\nProduction Status: Proof-of-concept validated (2/10 success with continuous bug)\nNext: Fix to isolated sessions, test on all 69 cleaned jobs	Session 1 Output: JSON array of skill objects with skill/evidence/confidence/category fields. Example: [{"skill":"SQL","evidence":"Managing licenses for over 80k users requires database queries","confidence":"high","category":"technical"}]\n\nSession 2 Output: JSON object with match_score (0-100), matching_skills array, relevant_experience, key_strengths, gaps, and recommendation. Example: {"match_score":45,"matching_skills":["Beratung","Kundenbeziehungen"],"relevant_experience":"Direct experience in