 of sustainability topics at a strategic level (Double Materiality) and coordinates responses to key ESG rating requests.ESG is a key element of the strategic priorities of the group-wide transformational strategy of Deutsche Bank. We are investing in the platforms, data and technology that will ensure we meet our ESG reporting requirements, and help our clients manage their Sustainability goals and transition to a Net Zero Carbon economy. The Chief Sustainability Office is partnering with Sustainability Technology to drive the Sustainability Data and Technology Programme. This is an outstanding opportunity for a Project Management professional to drive projects at the interface between the Chief Sustainability Office and TDI, incl. driving the development of the ESG Data workstream within the Sustainability Strategy KD and gain knowledge and experience in the fast-growing ESG market.Your key responsibilitiesYou support international projects at the interface between CSO and TDI in close cooperation with business and infrastructure functionsYou work closely with the Sustainability Data and Technology Programme lead, delivery teams and stakeholders to understand progress, resolve project blockers, ensure plans reflect reality, and to control the financial, resourcing and investment governance of the workstream.You actively manage risks, issues and dependencies with other functions and initiatives in the bank in line with bank governance standards.You will deal with various areas of the bank, ranging from business to infrastructure functions and interact with different levels of seniority, internally and externallyYour skills and experiencesYou are a University graduates with a Masters degree focusing on business and/or technology;You have strong project management experience including experience in managing international projects with multiple deliveriesYou have proven experience in optimizing and implementing processes, ideally including controlsYou are able to deliver quality even under time pressure, combined with strong analytical, conceptual problem-solving skills and excellent conflict resolution skills.You are able to manage multiple pieces of work, prioritise delivery as necessary & negotiate effectively with stakeholdersYou have a strong interest in ESG / sustainability an advantage, preferably proven by respective working experienceYou are fluent in English and GermanWhat we offerWe provide you with a comprehensive portfolio of benefits and offerings to support both, your private and professional needs.Emotionally and mentally balancedA positive mind helps us master the challenges of everyday life  both professionally and privately. We offer consultation in difficult life situations as well as mental health awareness trainings.Physically thrivingWe support you in staying physically fit through an offering to maintain personal health and a professional environment. You can benefit from health check-ups; vaccination drives as well as advice on healthy living and nutrition.Socially connectedNetworking opens up new perspectives, helps us thrive professionally and personally as well as strengthens our self-confidence and well-being. You can benefit from PME family service, FitnessCenter Job, flexible working (e.g parttime, hybrid working, job tandem) as well as an extensive culture of diversity, equity and inclusion.Financially secureWe provide you with financial security not only during your active career but also for the future. You can benefit from offerings such as pension plans, banking services, company bicycle or Deutschlandticket.Since our offerings slightly vary across locations, please contact your recruiter with specific questions.This job is available in full and parttime.In case of any recruitment related questions, please get in touch with Stefanie Schumann.Contact Stefanie Schumann: +49(69)910-42578 Wir streben eine Unternehmenskultur an, in der wir gemeinsam jeden Tag das Beste geben. Dazu gehren verantwortungsvolles Handeln, wirtschaftliches Denken, Initiative ergreifen und zielgerichtete Zusammenarbeit.Gemeinsam teilen und feiern wir die Erfolge unserer Mitarbeiter*innen. Gemeinsam sind wir die Deutsche Bank Gruppe.Wir begren Bewerbungen von allen Menschen und frdern ein positives, faires und integratives Arbeitsumfeld.	["managing international projects with multiple deliveriesYou have proven experience in optimizing and implementing processes", "the fast-growing ESG market.Your key responsibilitiesYou support international projects at the interface between CSO and TDI in close cooperation with business and infrastructure functionsYou work closely with the Sustainability Data and Technology Programme lead"]	Frankfurt	Hessen	Deutschland	f	Unbefristet	Vollzeit	kein Corporate Title	\N	[]	Deutsche Bank	Frankfurt	14	2025-07-08	/index.php?ac=jobad&id=65054	2025	2025-09-15 19:10:57	2025-09-15 19:10:57	t	[]	\N	\N
