em with internal and external partners.<br>    <br>- Took part in contract negotiations, managed changes in the vendor relationship and was responsible for the quality assurance of deliverables.|\\\\n|### 1998-1999|### Commerzbank, Application Architect, Frankfurt|\\\\n||Was project manager of project ZUM (Zentrales User-Management) in charge of designing and implementating centralized user and IT ressource requirements management (hardware, software) for the whole of Deutsche Post. In this role:<br><br>  <br><br>- Designed of first prototypes as proof of concept.<br>    <br>- Evaluated feasible software solutions.<br>    <br>- Managed selection process and onboarding of chosen supplier.<br>    <br>- Populated application with first set of data by integrating available data sources from LDAP and legacy systems.<br>    <br>- Coordinated application development, rollout and coaching of the new team.|\\\\n|### 1998|### F. Hoffmann \\\\u2013 La Roche, Rollout Manager, Basel|\\\\n||Worked as member of the development team for \\\\u201eCommon Office Environment\\\\u201c (COE/2.1) \\\\u2013 the standardized, Global Desktop environment of Client/Server-based systems.<br><br>  <br><br>- Evaluate and feed back user test results into procedures for global rollout and localization of installed systems.<br>    <br>- Documented core systems management processes, such as software distribution, license management and daily administrative tasks.|\\\\n|### 1997-1998|### Dresdner Bank, Information Architect, Frankfurt|\\\\n||Part of global effort to design and implement a new information desktop for Dresdner Private Banking:<br><br>  <br><br>- Collected information requirements through series of business managers worldwide.<br>    <br>- Distilled information requirements into an information desktop, which was presented to the global business manager community.<br>    <br>- Planned, staffed, and budgeted implementation of information desktop.|\\\\n|### 1996-1997|### Deutsche Bahn, Help